For purposes of this subsection, distance shall be measured by taking a one-
quarter-mile radial length from the lot boundaries of each CTfastrak station.
B.
Any use not supportive of transit-oriented development shall be prohibited until the
Town Council, acting as the Town's zoning authority, adopts revisions to the zoning
ordinances creating new transit-oriented development zoning or for nine months
following the effective date of this section, whichever is sooner.
C.
Uses not supportive of transit-oriented development include and are limited to the
following:
(1) Car wash facilities;
(2) Contractors yards;
(3) Drive-in facilities/drive-up windows accessory to any bank, restaurant, retail
pharmacy uses;
(4) Junkyards;
(5) Kennels;
(6) Motor vehicle sales, service and repair and gasoline service stations;
(7) Nurseries and greenhouses, including sales-area-goods pertinent thereto;
(8) Outdoor storage of material and equipment;
(9) Passenger automobile rental agencies;
(10) Vehicle-intensive businesses; and
(11) Wholesale business and storage warehouse uses.
